Almirall, Grifols, Viscofan: Iberian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 
2011-06-07T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/almirall-grifols-viscofan-iberian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  slid 1.2 percent to 10,157.70 in
 Madrid . Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  dropped 1.2 percent to 7,520.50.  Spanish stocks:        Almirall SA (ALM)  : The pharmaceutical company said in a
filing it won approval from authorities to start selling its
skin treatment Actikerall in the U.K. The stock fell 0.4 percent
to 7.51 euros.  Grifols SA (GRF SM): Europe’s largest maker of blood-plasma
products said in a statement it named Thomas Glanzmann as
chairman of the board of the company’s operations in the U.S.
The stock fell 1.53 percent to 13.85 euros.  Viscofan SA (VIS)  : The company said in a filing it will
post a one-time gain of 2.7 million euros in its first-half
results after settling a dispute over a  bank loan  to its Serbian
unit Koteks Viscofan DOO. The shares were unchanged at 28.54
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
